# Clerk Authentication & Data Isolation

All authentication must go through Clerk. Users must only ever access their own data.

## Server-side auth

In Server Components, Route Handlers, and Server Actions, always call `auth()` from `@clerk/nextjs/server`. Never trust a user ID from the request body, query params, URL segments, or client props.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — derive userId from the session
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) {
  // Server Component: no /sign-in page — redirect to homepage where sign-in/sign-up buttons live
  redirect("/");
  // Route Handler / Server Action: return 401
  // return new Response("Unauthorized", { status: 401 });
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — never trust caller-supplied IDs
async function getDecks(userId: string) { ... }  // userId came from the client
```

## Deck queries — always filter by clerkUserId

Every read, update, and delete on the `decks` table must include a `clerkUserId` condition. Inserts must set `clerkUserId` from `auth()`. See [db/schema.ts](mdc:db/schema.ts) and [db/index.ts](mdc:db/index.ts).

```typescript
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks } from "@/db/schema";
import { and, eq } from "drizzle-orm";

const { userId } = await auth();
if (!userId) redirect("/");

// ✅ Select — scoped to the authenticated user
const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));

// ✅ Insert — clerkUserId from auth(), never from the client
const [newDeck] = await db.insert(decks).values({ clerkUserId: userId, name, description }).returning();

// ✅ Update — combine id + clerkUserId so users can't mutate another user's deck
await db.update(decks).set({ name }).where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));

// ✅ Delete — same pattern
await db.delete(decks).where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));
```

## Card queries — scope through the owning deck

`cards` has no `clerkUserId` column; ownership is established via the FK to `decks`. Always verify deck ownership before accessing cards.

```typescript
import { cards, decks } from "@/db/schema";
import { and, eq } from "drizzle-orm";

// ✅ GOOD — verify deck ownership in the same query
const result = await db
  .select({ card: cards })
  .from(cards)
  .innerJoin(decks, eq(cards.deckId, decks.id))
  .where(and(eq(cards.deckId, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));

// ✅ GOOD — or check ownership before mutating
const [deck] = await db.select().from(decks).where(and(eq(decks.id, deckId), eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId)));
if (!deck) return new Response("Not found", { status: 404 });
await db.delete(cards).where(eq(cards.id, cardId));
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — querying cards without an ownership check on the parent deck
await db.select().from(cards).where(eq(cards.deckId, deckId));
```

## Client components

`useUser()` and `useAuth()` are only for UI state (showing names, toggling visible elements). Never use them to decide what data to fetch or render — that authorization must happen server-side.
